{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaa32c328-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3749"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3749"},"text":"§ 3749.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Burden of proof on contractor","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In a proceeding before the Armed Services Board of Contract Appeals, the United States Court of Federal Claims, or any other Federal court in which the reasonableness of indirect costs for which a contractor seeks reimbursement from the Department of Defense is in issue, the burden of proof shall be upon the contractor to establish that those costs are reasonable.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaa32c329-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added and amended ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXVIII/s1832/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XVIII, § 1832(a)","children":[],"tail":", (h), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4218"},"text":"134 Stat. 4218","children":[],"tail":", 4222.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idaa32c32a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idaa32c32b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idaa32c32c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The text of subsec. (j) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"hre